"2:196:67" : {s: 2, a: 196, w: 67, r: "وقي", t: "وَٱتَّقُوا۟", l: "ٱتَّقَىٰ", lc: 166, tl: "wa-ittaqū", lb: "কোনো কিছুর ব্যাপারে অত্যন্ত সচেতন থাকা, আল্লাহর প্রতি সচেতন থাকা",e: "And fear", b: "এবং তোমরা ভয় কর", i: "dan bertakwalah", f: 38, rm: "to protect, save, preserve, ward off, guard against evil and calamity, be secure, take as a shield, regard the duty. muttaqii - one who guard against evil and against that which harms and injures and is regardful of his duty towards human beings and God.", ag: "واو استئنافية وفعل أمر صيغة ٨ وضمير متصل ", eg: "Resumption wa and Verb Imperative 8th form and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPV", qual: "(VIII)", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "ٱتَّقَىٰ"},
"2:196:68" : {s: 2, a: 196, w: 68, r: "اله", t: "ٱللَّهَ", l: "ٱللَّه", lc: 2811, tl: "l-laha", lb: "আল্লাহ",e: "Allah", b: "আল্লাহকে", i: "Allah", f: 592, rm: "to serve, worship or adore; to protect, grant refuge, preserve save, rescue, liberate; object of worship ie God; (ا-ل-ل-ه) God, the one true God applied as a proper name denoting the true god, comprising all the excellent divine names; a unity comprising all the essences of existing things.", ag: "علم منصوب", eg: "Proper Accusative case", tag: "PN", pos: "PN", att: "ACC", qual: "", deg: "", gen: "", num: "", mood: "", lu: "إِلَٰهٌۭ"},
"2:196:69" : {s: 2, a: 196, w: 69, r: "علم", t: "وَٱعْلَمُوٓا۟", l: "عَلِمَ", lc: 382, tl: "wa-iʿ'lamū", lb: "(সে) জানে",e: "and know", b: "এবং তোমরা জেনে রাখ", i: "dan ketahuilah", f: 18, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows.", ag: "واو عطف وفعل أمر وضمير متصل ", eg: "Conjunction wa and Verb Imperative and Pronoun suffix ", tag: "V", pos: "V", att: "IMPV", qual: "", deg: "2", gen: "M", num: "P", mood: "", lu: "أَعْلَمُ،عَلِمَ،عَلِيمٌۢ"},
